# Student Risk Identification Model
### Data Science Task – Jan 2026

## Overview
Proactively identify students at risk of not completing their studies using academic, attendance, and financial data — enabling support teams to intervene early with targeted action plans.

---

## Step 1 – Data Preparation & Quality Issues

| Issue | Problem | Solution |
|---|---|---|
| **Inconsistency** | Mixed gender labels (`Male` vs `M`), inconsistent date formats | Standardised to single-character codes, unified dates to `DD/MM/YYYY` |
| **Anomalies** | Duplicate record for Student 1006; non-numeric `.` in `CreditsCompleted` | Removed duplicates; replaced invalid entries with `NaN` |
| **Missing Values** | Nulls in `AttendanceRate` and `LastAttendanceDate` | Treated as **High Risk signals** — absence of data = warning flag |

---

## Step 2 – Methodology: Weighted Scoring Model

| Category | Weight | Key Metrics |
|---|---|---|
| **Engagement** | 50% | Attendance Rate, Last Attendance Date |
| **Academic** | 30% | Credits Completed, Last Assessment Submission |
| **Financial & Status** | 20% | Outstanding Fees, Scholarship, Enrolment Status |

> **Rationale**: Disengagement almost always precedes formal withdrawal — making engagement the strongest lead indicator.

---

## Step 3 – Model Output & At-Risk Students

| Student ID | Risk Score | Risk Band | Key Flag |
|---|---|---|---|
| Student 1003 | 1.25 / 10 | 🔴 Critical | Suspended, £3,500 debt, no attendance since 2025 |
| Student 1002 | 2.75 / 10 | 🟠 High | Active but 45% attendance, no recent logins |
| Student 1005 | 3.10 / 10 | 🟠 High | Known withdrawal — used to validate model |
| Student 1001 | 6.50 / 10 | 🟢 Low | On track |
| Student 1004 | 7.20 / 10 | 🟢 Low | On track |
| Student 1006 | 7.80 / 10 | 🟢 Low | On track |

> **Lower score = Higher risk.** Risk threshold set at 4.0.

---

## Step 4 – Limitations & Future Improvements

### Current Limitations
- **Small Sample Size** – Snapshot data; no long-term trends or seasonal patterns.
- **Static Snapshot** – Scores are point-in-time; situations may have already changed.
- **Missing Behavioural Data** – No VLE login frequency or engagement depth.

### Future Improvements
- **VLE Integration** – Login frequency and resource access as leading indicators.
- **Live Dashboard** – Auto-refresh scores when lectures or deadlines are missed.
- **Longitudinal Dataset** – Train predictive models on historical cohorts for better accuracy.

